In 2020, the Executive led the charge as state machinery was deployed to commit arson, abduction, extrajudicial killings, arbitrary detentions, abuse and molestation of citizens, activists and legislators, the demolition of dwellings, destruction of food crops and violent suppression of peaceful assemblies and processions. 

The mandate to manage the Covid-19 pandemic was recharacterised as a policing, not medical issue, and reassigned from the Ministry of Health to the Ministry of the Interior. The Ministry of Health today remains a diffident announcer of statistics. 

@EricNgeno The DP made the announcement shortly after President Uhuru Kenyatta banned all political gatherings for 30 days. The President has also announced that funerals will take place 72 hours after confirmation of death. This was the President's 14th address on the Covid-19 pandemic in kenya, and the first one in 2021.